cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.HC 

This paper deals with activity recognition in first-person videos using audio-visual features. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses multi-modal features, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques such as multi-kernel learning and boosting, which could place it in categories such as cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper mentions applications such as lifelogging and assisted-living, which suggests a potential connection to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
